Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "ljubazan":

1. On je jako *ljubazan*. (He is very kind.)
2. *Ljubazno* je pozdravio komšiju. (He greeted his neighbor kindly.)
3. Da bi bili uspešni u poslu, morate biti *ljubazni* prema klijentima. (To be successful in business, you need to be courteous to your clients.)
4. Sestra je *ljubazno* ponudila da mi pomogne oko spremanja. (My sister kindly offered to help me with cleaning.)
5. Oni su *ljubazni* prema gostima u svojoj kući. (They are kind to guests in their home.)
6. *Ljubaznost* je bitna karakteristika za uspostavljanje dobrih odnosa. (Kindness is an important trait for establishing good relationships.)
7. Bila je veoma *ljubazna* dok mi je objašnjavala kako da stignem do tamo. (She was very polite while explaining to me how to get there.)
8. Molim vas da budete *ljubazni* i uklonite svoje stvari sa stola. (Please be kind and remove your things from the table.)
9. Ona se uvek *ljubazno* smeje našim šalama. (She always kindly laughs at our jokes.)
10. Kada ste *ljubazni* prema drugima, obično dobijete isto u povratku. (When you are kind to others, you usually get the same in return.)

Note: The star symbol (*) is used only to highlight the Serbian word "ljubazan" in each sentence.